PDVSA’s Cardon Refinery Rocked by Explosion, Notifalcon Says

-- B y   N a t h a n   C r o o k s
-- 
2011-05-23T17:37:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/pdvsa-s-cardon-refinery-rocked-by-explosion-notifalcon-says.html
Petroleos de  Venezuela  SA’s Cardon
refinery in western Venezuela had an explosion today at its
catalytic cracking unit, news agency Notifalcon reported on its
 website , without saying where it got the information.  The explosion damaged the unit, Notifalcon said, without
specifying the amount of damage or how production was affected.  Plant workers were evacuated, and the situation has been
controlled, Notifalcon, based in Punto Fijo, Venezuela,
reported.  The refinery, part of the Paraguana Refining Complex in
Falcon state, was shut by a  power outage  on May 12.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Crooks in Santiago at 
 ncrooks@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  